DOMMatrixRotateSelf.summary: The rotateSelf() method of the interface is a mutable transformation method that modifies a matrix. It rotates the source matrix around each of its axes by the specified number of degrees and returns the rotated matrix.

remarks.para: To rotate a matrix without mutating it, see

-CSS transform property
-CSS rotate property
-CSS transform-function functions-transform-function/rotate
-transform-function/rotate3d
-transform-function/rotateX
-transform-function/rotateY
